@dannysmyda: do you mean "just throw a SQLException"?
I can certainly use try-with-resource in the method to manage the resources, but at this time Id prefer to not change the return value type.  I think the way this and other similar methods are used, is currently expecting a boolean return value.
And this is going to get used in the upgrade path as well, and may further have some conflicts with changes Greg is making.
